Count 1 - Fail/Inform Required Construction Permits - No contest plea.   
Count 2 - Failure to Describe Work/Products in Home - No contest plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 3.   Motion granted.   Sentences are withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) Maintain full-time employment or work search combination; 
3) Have no contact with any of the victims, Kayla Yurk, Mathilda & Donald Goeke, Mark Korleski, David Cole, Kenneth Klusmeyer, and Anna & James Malik; 
4) Defendant must obtain building permits for all jobs he obtains estimates on or works on. (No permit, no work);
5) All proposed contracts/estimates must comply with Wisconsin Statutes and the Wisconsin Administrative Code ATCP Chapter 110; 
6) Defendant will provide written verification that all sources of supply are paid and no money is owing within 15 business days of completing any job or contract;
7) All jobs must have a written conract or estimate; 
8) All funds collected from persons who accepted an estimate or contract shll be held, received and disbursed as required by Chapter 779, Wis. Stats;
9) Forfty-five (45) days jail, Seven (7) days, up front, under the Huber law, to commence on 03-02-17 by 5:00 p.m.  Thirty-eight (38) days stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion; 
10) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharges;
11) Pay costs of action; 
12) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.   
Defendant is given 1 day credit.
